Document: SkeletonModification2DLookAt
Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonmodification2dlookat.rst
Summary: Exposes methods for controlling the look-at behavior and constraints of a SkeletonModification2D.

Methods
* get_additional_rotation() → float: Returns the additional rotation applied to the bone.
* get_constraint_angle_invert() → bool: Returns whether the constraint angle is inverted.
* get_constraint_angle_max() → float: Returns the maximum constraint angle.
* get_constraint_angle_min() → float: Returns the minimum constraint angle.
* get_enable_constraint() → bool: Returns whether the constraint is enabled.
* set_additional_rotation(rotation: float) → void: Sets the additional rotation applied to the bone.
* set_constraint_angle_invert(invert: bool) → void: Sets whether the constraint angle is inverted.
* set_constraint_angle_max(angle_max: float) → void: Sets the maximum constraint angle.
* set_constraint_angle_min(angle_min: float) → void: Sets the minimum constraint angle.
* set_enable_constraint(enable_constraint: bool) → void: Sets whether the constraint is enabled.
